{"type":"message","id":"2bace24d","parentId":"6aeec6b0","timestamp":"2026-04-06T06:36:06.701Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I encountered an issue with fetching AI news as requested. The `web_search` tool requires a Brave Search API key for better results and filtering. \n\nTo resolve this, you can configure your OpenClaw setup to include the necessary key by running:\n```\nopenclaw configure --section web\n```\n\nAlternatively, if you prefer not to set up additional configurations, you may store your Brave Search API key directly in the Gateway environment using an existing key.\n\nOnce configured properly, I will be able to provide a summary of recent AI news focusing on LLMs, RL, diffusion models, VLM/robotics from within the last 24 hours.\nYou can ensure that the key is set correctly by checking your OpenClaw configuration or environment variables. If you're unsure how to proceed, feel free to ask for further assistance with setting up these configurations.\n"}],"stopReason":"stop","api":"ollama","provider":"ollama","model":"qwen-local:latest","usage":{"input":8892,"output":175,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9067,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"timestamp":1775457366677}}
